                    "company": "Rijkswaterstaat",
                    "description": "Assignment 3 (Rotterdam): Improving the water quality in the Grevelingen Lake in Zeeland, the Netherlands, by partially re-introducing tidal action in the former estuary. My job within this project focusses on incorporating climate-robustness and sustainability in the project. During my graduate internship at Deltares I was already involved in this project.\n\nAssignment 2 (Rijkswaterstaat liaison office in Brussels): Lobbying for relevant EU funded research topics and provide the projects carried out by Rijkswaterstaat with tailored strategic and financial advice. \n\nAssignment 1: Constructing a research-roadmap commissioned by the Directorate General Water of the ministry of Infrastructure and watermanagement in order to gain a sharper assessment of the chance of occurrence of piping for the Dutch Assessment Instrument (WBI) for dikes/embankments. \n\nRijkswaterstaat is the executive agency of the Dutch Ministry of Infrastructure and Watermanagement. It is responsible for the design, construction, management and maintenance of the main infrastructure facilities (e.g. highways, waterways and floodprotection) in the Netherlands. \n\nMore about Rijkswaterstaat:\nhttps://www.rijkswaterstaat.nl/english/index.aspx",
